1
00:00:00,360 --> 00:00:04,570
Hide well, or else I can see your hair!
 [Episode 19]

2
00:00:04,570 --> 00:00:08,910
Hide well, or else I can see your hair!

3
00:00:08,910 --> 00:00:13,290
Hide well, or else I can see your hair!

4
00:00:13,290 --> 00:00:16,250
I'll look for you now.

5
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:24,180
Hide well, or else I can see your hair!

6
00:00:24,180 --> 00:00:26,470
Are you here?

7
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:33,260
Stay still! If you move now, I'll get caught too!

8
00:01:01,510 --> 00:01:06,930
I found you! Oh, yeah! Dad, you're the tagger now!

9
00:01:06,930 --> 00:01:11,960
Ms. Park Noona, you're such a bad team player! How can you push me for you to survive?

10
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:15,280
Because of you, now I'm the tagger!

11
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:18,030
Wow, you're so mean.

12
00:01:18,030 --> 00:01:20,550
No, it's not like that.

13
00:01:20,550 --> 00:01:24,860
Why did you have to follow me to my hiding place?

14
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:28,790
There were lots of other places you could have hidden.

15
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:36,380
But why is my heart so tingling and painful?

16
00:01:38,330 --> 00:01:40,760
What's going on?

17
00:01:42,110 --> 00:01:44,940
- Dad!
- Dad!

18
00:01:44,940 --> 00:01:48,800
Dad, what's wrong? Aren't you feeling well?

19
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:53,800
I'm fine. Maybe I'm feeling the post-injury symptoms.

20
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:59,040
I think you guys should continue the game without me. I'll go in and rest for a bit.

21
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:09,360
What's that? I just caught my dad.

22
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:14,020
Is he running away because he doesn't want to be the tagger?

23
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:32,100
Chairman, what's wrong? Are you feeling sick?

24
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:37,060
Chief Jo Noona. Something's wrong with my heart.

25
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:39,960
Your heart? What's wrong with it?

26
00:02:39,960 --> 00:02:44,390
I think my heart was injured as well

27
00:02:44,390 --> 00:02:47,010
when I got hurt in the mountains.

28
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:52,520
In what way is it weird? If you injured your heart, it's a big deal!

29
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:55,350
Tell me the symptoms in more detail.

30
00:02:55,350 --> 00:03:00,280
It happened all of a sudden while I was playing hide and seek with the kids.

31
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:04,520
I ended up hiding with Ms. Park Noona behind the tree,

32
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:07,920
and my heart started beating like crazy.

33
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:11,480
Were you hiding with Ms. Park?

34
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:16,650
Yes, I didn't run that hard. But my heart started beating hard.

35
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:23,940
So much so that I thought it would jump out of my body.

36
00:03:23,940 --> 00:03:29,420
But it's strange. It got fine now.

37
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:35,000
What is this? He doesn't remember Ms. Park,

38
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:40,610
but did his feelings for Ms. Park revive and express through his body?

39
00:03:40,610 --> 00:03:43,140
No, it can't be.

40
00:03:44,570 --> 00:03:49,550
Isn't it strange how it happened so suddenly? Should I get my heart checked out?

41
00:03:49,550 --> 00:03:53,910
Yes, I think that would be the best.

42
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:59,880
My memory is broken and what if my heart is broken too?

43
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:05,890
No, it's not. You were healthy before. I'm sure you are fine.

44
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:08,530
Then, Chief Jo Noona,

45
00:04:08,530 --> 00:04:15,480
can you go to the hospital with me?

46
00:04:15,490 --> 00:04:21,440
Of course. I will be with you.

47
00:04:24,570 --> 00:04:30,540
We examined through ultrasound, and nothing was wrong. So don't worry about it, Chairman Lee.

48
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:33,270
Is that so?

49
00:04:33,270 --> 00:04:36,890
But why did my heart beat so fast earlier?

50
00:04:36,890 --> 00:04:42,380
It could happen. If you exercise hard or get surprised,

51
00:04:42,380 --> 00:04:46,620
or if you see someone you especially like.

52
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:51,070
I was only playing hide and seek with my children.

53
00:04:51,070 --> 00:04:55,660
Maybe it was because you got excited with the kids in a while.

54
00:04:55,660 --> 00:04:59,000
It could happen when you are having too much fun.

55
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,870
Oh, is that so?

56
00:05:14,510 --> 00:05:18,060
Ms. Park Noona, what brings you here?

57
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:23,390
I heard you went to the hospital.

58
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:29,000
I was worried if something went wrong with you

59
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:34,110
because I pushed you earlier and made you startled.

60
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:37,300
Well,

61
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:40,890
I didn't want to tell you because I didn't want you to feel guilty.

62
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:43,810
But since you asked, I have to tell you.

63
00:05:43,810 --> 00:05:49,330
Actually, something went wrong with my heart because you startled me earlier.

64
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:54,170
So, I need to get surgery.

65
00:05:54,170 --> 00:05:56,020
Really?

66
00:05:56,020 --> 00:06:00,450
Did that serious issue happen because of me?

67
00:06:00,450 --> 00:06:05,030
What do we do? I'm so sorry, Chairman.

68
00:06:05,030 --> 00:06:08,340
I am kidding. It's just a joke.

69
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:17,180
Did you say you were kidding?

70
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:19,730
Did you really believe what I said?

71
00:06:19,730 --> 00:06:25,860
You're not an elementary school kid. How can you believe me when I was just kidding?

72
00:06:25,860 --> 00:06:31,320
Why are you acting like this, Chairman? How can you joke about something like that?

73
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:34,200
You must have believed me looking at your being angry.

74
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:39,380
Who believes in a story about needing heart surgery because of a startle?

75
00:06:39,380 --> 00:06:43,760
Does it make sense? I don't think even Se Jong would fall for something like that.

76
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:48,890
You are really naive, Ms. Park Noona.

77
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:56,540
So you're saying that you are fine right now.

78
00:06:56,540 --> 00:07:02,090
Yes, I'm fine. The doctor said there's no problem.

79
00:07:02,130 --> 00:07:06,590
Okay, I get it. I'll get going.

80
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:12,630
What's up with her? Is she a dummy?

81
00:07:12,630 --> 00:07:16,920
How can she be so naive? It's hilarious.

82
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:27,170
What was that? He's so annoying!

83
00:07:27,170 --> 00:07:30,440
I'd give him a hit on the head if I could.

84
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:36,030
But I can't even do that. I shouldn't have asked.

85
00:07:36,030 --> 00:07:39,080
Ms. Park.

86
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:43,260
Were you coming out of the Chairman's study just now?

87
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:45,140
Yes.

88
00:07:45,140 --> 00:07:48,890
Why? Did he call you?

89
00:07:48,890 --> 00:07:51,800
No, he didn't.

90
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:56,590
But while we were playing hide and seek, he said his heart didn't feel right,

91
00:07:56,590 --> 00:08:00,330
so I was worried, and I had to ask him about it.

92
00:08:00,330 --> 00:08:02,300
Ms. Park.

93
00:08:02,300 --> 00:08:04,830
Why would you worry about that?

94
00:08:04,830 --> 00:08:06,470
Pardon?

95
00:08:06,470 --> 00:08:09,220
You don't have to worry about the Chairman.

96
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:12,970
And please refrain from going into his study from now on.

97
00:08:12,970 --> 00:08:17,130
If you have anything to converse with him, speak to me first.

98
00:08:17,130 --> 00:08:19,940
I am in charge of everything in this household.

99
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:24,960
Yes. I understand.

100
00:08:31,930 --> 00:08:37,880
It's not like I can stay in this house and watch her 24/7.

101
00:08:37,910 --> 00:08:40,820
That's right!

102
00:08:47,910 --> 00:08:51,820
Chairman, I brought you some snacks.

103
00:08:51,820 --> 00:08:55,570
Wow, it's my favorite chocolate cake.

104
00:08:55,570 --> 00:08:59,190
You are the best, Chief Jo Noona.

105
00:09:00,590 --> 00:09:06,680
I have something to discuss with you.

106
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:08,370
What is it?

107
00:09:08,370 --> 00:09:13,380
It looks like it's too much for Ms. Park to take care of the children on her own.

108
00:09:13,380 --> 00:09:17,530
That being the case, and since I've come back as well,

109
00:09:17,530 --> 00:09:22,910
how about if we make Ms. Park work during the day only?

110
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:29,230
We can't do that without asking the children.

111
00:09:29,230 --> 00:09:32,150
But, why?

112
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:35,580
I will be here at night instead of Ms. Park.

113
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:41,420
It would allow me to get close to the children before we get married.

114
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:45,500
Why would you ask the children?

115
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:49,800
Things like this are up to you and me.

116
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:54,550
We can't have it that way.

117
00:09:54,550 --> 00:09:57,710
What do you mean?

118
00:09:57,710 --> 00:10:04,450
When I dismissed Ms. Park last time without talking to the children, they were very upset.

119
00:10:04,450 --> 00:10:06,790
So I made a promise to them.

120
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:09,310
I would make decisions about things that involve the children

121
00:10:09,310 --> 00:10:13,720
by talking to them democratically first.

122
00:10:17,270 --> 00:10:20,940
Why did you gather all of us? What do you want to say?

123
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:23,560
I have something to discuss with you.

124
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:29,510
I promised to discuss democratically with you guys about things that affect you.

125
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:32,290
I am one who keeps promises.

126
00:10:32,290 --> 00:10:35,550
So, what do you want to discuss with us?

127
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:39,450
As you know, Ms. Park is a live-in tutor.

128
00:10:39,450 --> 00:10:42,870
But what if we switch her to only work in the daytime?

129
00:10:42,870 --> 00:10:47,530
Because Chief Jo Noona wants to stay here and look after you guys.

130
00:10:47,530 --> 00:10:49,250
What do you guys think?

131
00:10:49,250 --> 00:10:55,760
So are you saying switch the roles of Ms. Park and Chief Jo?

132
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,570
To simply put, that's what I'm saying.

133
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:58,630
I don't want that.

134
00:10:58,630 --> 00:10:59,990
It's a no for me too.

135
00:10:59,990 --> 00:11:05,860
I can't sleep if Ms. Park doesn't read for me at night.

136
00:11:05,860 --> 00:11:09,300
Did Ms. Park ask to work during the day only?

137
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:12,650
Did she say it's difficult for her to live with us here?

138
00:11:12,650 --> 00:11:14,480
No, it's not that.

139
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:19,960
Chief Jo wants to stay here so she can get close to you.

140
00:11:21,450 --> 00:11:25,120
Dad, we three are completely in opposition.

141
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:28,110
Do you understand?

142
00:11:28,110 --> 00:11:29,590
Yes, I do.

143
00:11:29,590 --> 00:11:31,710
Your opinions are the most important.

144
00:11:31,710 --> 00:11:37,130
I will follow your opinions and not make the change.

145
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:41,480
Children, don't you like that your dad's democratic?

146
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:45,470
Dad, please do not say a word of this to Ms. Park.

147
00:11:45,470 --> 00:11:48,670
It would only hurt her feelings.

148
00:11:48,670 --> 00:11:51,520
Okay, I got it.

149
00:12:00,380 --> 00:12:04,280
What did the children say? Did it go well?

150
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:10,530
Well, the children don't want it. All three of them.

151
00:12:10,530 --> 00:12:13,370
I beg your pardon?

152
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:18,130
It's not like she's quitting. They don't like Ms. Park commuting?

153
00:12:18,130 --> 00:12:20,280
No.

154
00:12:20,280 --> 00:12:22,810
A home tutor is there for the children.

155
00:12:22,810 --> 00:12:25,780
If the children don't like it, then we shouldn't make a change.

156
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:30,180
We should leave it as it is.

157
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:37,340
I feel like the children only think of me as a housekeeper.

158
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:42,520
So I wanted to get closer to them before we got married.

159
00:12:42,520 --> 00:12:47,660
Okay then, why don't we tell the children that we are getting married?

160
00:12:47,660 --> 00:12:50,470
That's the only way I can get close to them.

161
00:12:50,470 --> 00:12:54,550
Didn't you say you didn't want to surprise the children?

162
00:12:54,550 --> 00:12:58,090
Since Jenny is a sensitive teenager facing the final exams,

163
00:12:58,090 --> 00:13:01,230
you said we should wait until she's done with the exams.

164
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:06,060
I did say that back then...

165
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:12,800
Right, if Jenny finds out her dad and I are getting married, she would go outrageous.

166
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:15,530
She would ask when we started dating, was it before her mom died,

167
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:17,840
and oppose the marriage no matter what.

168
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:24,130
She would meet up with Lawyer Koh and check what's going on and make me go crazy.

169
00:13:26,290 --> 00:13:30,390
I get it. Should I go now and tell them that we are getting married?

170
00:13:30,390 --> 00:13:35,910
No! Let's wait until Jenny finishes her final exams.

171
00:13:35,910 --> 00:13:38,050
Okay, then. As soon as Jenny finishes her exams,

172
00:13:38,050 --> 00:13:40,430
I will take her for pizza and tell her.

173
00:13:40,430 --> 00:13:42,470
I will tell Se Chan and Se Jong too.

174
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:45,890
I have to tell them as their father.

175
00:13:47,770 --> 00:13:50,530
Yes, that would be the best.

176
00:13:50,530 --> 00:13:54,500
You are absolutely right.

177
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:03,240
But, even if he's gone back to being a stupid 22 years old.

178
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:08,130
How can he be shifted around by his children like that?

179
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:14,700
But what if he falls for Ms. Park again?

180
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:19,440
No, he wouldn't do that this time.

181
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:23,880
He totally fell for me, so it won't happen again.

182
00:14:27,670 --> 00:14:31,530
Se Chan, what brings you here?

183
00:14:31,530 --> 00:14:34,670
I have something to ask you.

184
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:36,050
Okay, what is it?

185
00:14:36,050 --> 00:14:37,820
Chief Jo.

186
00:14:37,820 --> 00:14:45,810
Did you ask my dad for Ms. Park to come to work in the morning and get off in the evening?

187
00:14:45,810 --> 00:14:47,720
What?

188
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,990
What's this?

189
00:14:48,990 --> 00:14:55,590
Did he tell all the details to the children? It's ridiculous!

190
00:14:55,590 --> 00:14:59,160
Yes, I did. Why?

191
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:02,220
Even if my dad reverted to 22 years old,

192
00:15:02,220 --> 00:15:07,060
you can't just push things around as you want!

193
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:10,580
- What?
- Ms. Park is a precious person to us.

194
00:15:10,580 --> 00:15:14,030
We barely stopped her from leaving our house.

195
00:15:14,030 --> 00:15:18,100
Please don't say anything regarding Ms. Park from now on!

196
00:15:18,100 --> 00:15:23,920
It's not like you are paying her wages.

197
00:15:29,430 --> 00:15:34,670
What did he just say to me?

198
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:37,920
My goodness!

199
00:15:52,330 --> 00:15:56,600
What are you saying?

200
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:59,990
What do you mean by clear it out by today?

201
00:15:59,990 --> 00:16:03,300
Mr. Park Soo Chul, I'm sorry.

202
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:06,650
The economy is bad, so to cut labor costs,

203
00:16:06,650 --> 00:16:10,500
they are reducing staff. I couldn't help it.

204
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:15,120
Since you are not a permanent employee, that's what happened.

205
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:19,000
Even so, how can you say that without any notice?

206
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,500
I'm sorry.

207
00:16:20,500 --> 00:16:23,570
I couldn't do anything about it.

208
00:16:23,570 --> 00:16:26,420
But you are still young.

209
00:16:26,420 --> 00:16:29,910
I'm sure you will find something good.

210
00:16:29,910 --> 00:16:32,510
Okay.

211
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:35,110
I understand.

212
00:16:45,220 --> 00:16:48,620
Driver Park, what brings you here?

213
00:16:48,620 --> 00:16:52,360
I am leaving my job here today.

214
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:55,730
So I wanted to say goodbye.

215
00:16:55,730 --> 00:16:58,120
What?

216
00:16:58,130 --> 00:17:00,490
Are you quit working here?

217
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:02,970
Why all of a sudden?

218
00:17:02,970 --> 00:17:05,780
It just happened.

219
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:10,580
You gifted this scarf to me.

220
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:15,530
I've been grateful to you for many things.

221
00:17:15,530 --> 00:17:17,230
Okay.

222
00:17:17,230 --> 00:17:20,220
I have been grateful to you as well.

223
00:17:20,220 --> 00:17:23,810
I've felt secure because you were here.

224
00:17:28,060 --> 00:17:30,950
I'll get going now.

225
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:34,380
Please stay healthy, CEO.

226
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:59,860
Dan Dan's father.

227
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:04,850
It was so good to see you at least like this way.

228
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:10,180
Please stay healthy for the sake of Dan Dan.

229
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:22,020
I hope this lunch box can cheer up Soo Chul!

230
00:18:22,020 --> 00:18:23,840
So that he will work hard,

231
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:28,460
and he'll become permanent and stay here for a long time.

232
00:18:28,460 --> 00:18:29,960
What brings you here?

233
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:33,260
Hello. I'm just here to give this lunch box and go.

234
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:37,160
I put a lot of bulgogi and japchae here,

235
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:40,910
so please feel free to eat it with my husband.

236
00:18:40,910 --> 00:18:44,100
But I don't see Soo Chul in here.

237
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:47,210
Do you mean Mr. Park Soo Chul?

238
00:18:47,210 --> 00:18:50,380
He quit here earlier today.

239
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:52,660
Pardon? What did you say?

240
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:54,460
What are you saying right now?

241
00:18:54,460 --> 00:18:57,460
He left for work this morning, but what do you mean he quit?

242
00:18:57,460 --> 00:18:59,750
What are you saying?

243
00:18:59,750 --> 00:19:03,930
It just happened that way because we had to reduce staff.

244
00:19:03,930 --> 00:19:06,230
Are you saying my husband got laid off?

245
00:19:06,230 --> 00:19:09,870
My husband? Why?

246
00:19:14,820 --> 00:19:16,990
Honey!

247
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:21,120
Did you leave without saying anything because they asked you to?

248
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:24,190
What can I do? I was only a contract employee.

249
00:19:24,190 --> 00:19:28,180
Even if you're a contract employee, how can they lay you off in a day?

250
00:19:28,180 --> 00:19:31,910
You worked so hard all this time.

251
00:19:31,910 --> 00:19:34,740
The company's situation is bad. I can't do anything about it.

252
00:19:34,740 --> 00:19:39,100
Why do you care about the company's situation? We're going to starve to death!

253
00:19:39,100 --> 00:19:41,950
How can you just quit because they asked you to?

254
00:19:41,950 --> 00:19:45,520
You should have laid down on the floor and fought for your job.

255
00:19:45,520 --> 00:19:50,520
- That's enough.
- How can you say that? We're going to starve to death now!

256
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:54,880
Finding a job is like catching a star. What are we going to do now?

257
00:19:54,880 --> 00:19:57,520
You have no place to work right now!

258
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,990
My goodness.

259
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:05,790
Honey, we have to come up with a plan!

260
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:10,760
What is going on?

261
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:14,630
- Did Son-in-law Park lose his job?
- Yes!

262
00:20:14,630 --> 00:20:19,430
He just left the company because they asked him to.

263
00:20:19,430 --> 00:20:22,650
He should have fought and stayed no matter what.

264
00:20:22,650 --> 00:20:25,180
What are we going to do now?

265
00:20:25,180 --> 00:20:28,040
Is there a bad spirit attached to this family or something?

266
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:31,140
Why does nothing work out for us?

267
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:39,960
Geon and Dae Beom's business is not going well. And now Son-in-law Park lost his job.

268
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:43,270
I don't know.

269
00:20:51,990 --> 00:20:57,470
Hey, we've sold six chicken skewers in five hours.

270
00:20:57,470 --> 00:21:01,390
This is the worst! I think it's the worst.

271
00:21:01,390 --> 00:21:05,470
We're wearing sleeveless in this cold weather, but it's useless.

272
00:21:05,470 --> 00:21:07,780
Hey, for this month,

273
00:21:07,780 --> 00:21:13,130
we earned less than a quarter of what I made from driving.

274
00:21:13,130 --> 00:21:16,780
