283
00:21:44,810 --> 00:21:48,140
Garbage food? How can you speak like that?

284
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:51,750
Ajumeoni, why are you picking a fight at someone's business?

285
00:21:51,750 --> 00:21:55,410
Picking a fight? My child ate a chicken skewer here,

286
00:21:55,410 --> 00:21:57,790
and almost died from a stomach ache all day.

287
00:21:57,790 --> 00:22:02,270
How are you going to compensate for my child's stomach ache?

288
00:22:02,270 --> 00:22:05,380
Stomach ache? It couldn't be.

289
00:22:05,380 --> 00:22:09,060
How do you know the stomach ache is not from something else?

290
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:11,790
We use fresh chicken every day.

291
00:22:11,790 --> 00:22:13,850
What? Fresh chicken, my foot!

292
00:22:13,850 --> 00:22:17,120
My son didn't eat anything else but this chicken skewer!

293
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:21,130
Listen, everyone, please do not eat chicken skewers from here. They are all garbage!

294
00:22:21,130 --> 00:22:24,050
- That's not true!
- My child ate a chicken skewer from here

295
00:22:24,050 --> 00:22:28,060
and almost died from stomach ache! It's all garbage here!

296
00:22:28,060 --> 00:22:33,150
What proof do you have that your son got sick from eating our chicken skewers?

297
00:22:33,150 --> 00:22:35,500
My goodness, are you going to hit me now?

298
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:38,020
Go ahead and hit me! Hit me!

299
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:43,080
You make my son get sick with this garbage, and now you are going to hit me!

300
00:22:43,080 --> 00:22:46,360
You have to go bankrupt to get yourself together!

301
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:48,100
Ajumma!

302
00:22:48,100 --> 00:22:50,230
Hey, hey.

303
00:22:51,860 --> 00:22:56,600
Ajumeoni, how can you do this with the food people eat?

304
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:59,870
Just hit me then. Chicken skewers don't have a fault!

305
00:22:59,870 --> 00:23:02,930
I'm going to report you to the police!

306
00:23:02,930 --> 00:23:06,320
I'm going to send you to jail for selling spoiled food!

307
00:23:06,320 --> 00:23:09,210
Just report us. Go ahead and report!

308
00:23:09,210 --> 00:23:11,700
I will not let your business run.

309
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:16,220
I'll make you can't run the business anymore, so we'll see!

310
00:23:51,490 --> 00:23:55,170
Brother-in-law!

311
00:23:55,170 --> 00:23:57,940
Father.

312
00:23:59,960 --> 00:24:05,050
Father, why are you doing that?

313
00:24:19,020 --> 00:24:21,940
I'm sorry.

314
00:24:24,780 --> 00:24:28,290
Why are you sorry?

315
00:24:28,290 --> 00:24:30,840
You didn't do anything to be sorry.

316
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:34,620
I didn't want you to see me like this.

317
00:24:34,620 --> 00:24:40,190
I wanted to succeed and pay you back.

318
00:24:40,190 --> 00:24:42,610
Father.

319
00:24:42,610 --> 00:24:46,020
Why am I like this?

320
00:24:47,910 --> 00:24:52,110
Why am I in this state?

321
00:24:56,600 --> 00:25:02,050
I never asked you to pay me back.

322
00:25:02,050 --> 00:25:04,690
Dae Beom.

323
00:25:04,690 --> 00:25:09,020
Who in this world never fails?

324
00:25:09,020 --> 00:25:11,460
When things don't work out, you try it again.

325
00:25:11,460 --> 00:25:15,960
If that fails, you try again. That's all.

326
00:25:19,050 --> 00:25:23,050
Father, it's cold. Why don't you go home?

327
00:25:23,050 --> 00:25:27,780
Also, please do not come back here.

328
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:30,910
I will go now.

329
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:52,710
Oh, yeah! Awesome! I've finally finished it.

330
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:56,880
I made this difficult thing. I'm great!

331
00:25:56,880 --> 00:26:00,380
Two hours of focused work paid off.

332
00:26:00,380 --> 00:26:04,430
I have to record this moment.

333
00:26:06,660 --> 00:26:10,650
Wow, Hyung, that's amazing! Did you make this?

334
00:26:10,650 --> 00:26:16,450
Lee Se Jong, don't touch it. Don't touch it!

335
00:26:16,450 --> 00:26:19,280
Hyung...

336
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:25,030
Hey, Lee Se Jong! I told you not to touch it!

337
00:26:29,540 --> 00:26:33,010
Lee Se Chan!

338
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:40,700
Lee Se Chan, what are you doing to Se Jong!

339
00:26:40,700 --> 00:26:45,190
He broke my robot I worked for two hours to complete!

340
00:26:45,190 --> 00:26:49,580
Are you saying you hit Se Jong for a mere robot? What is so important about this!

341
00:26:49,580 --> 00:26:52,570
How can an older brother hit a younger brother?

342
00:26:52,570 --> 00:26:57,330
How can you be so horrible and have no consideration? Who do you get that from?

343
00:26:57,330 --> 00:26:58,860
Chief Jo!

344
00:26:58,860 --> 00:27:02,350
Se Jong did wrong in the first place!

345
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:04,920
Oh, my, how dare you yell at me?

346
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:07,680
How can you speak back to an adult like that?

347
00:27:07,680 --> 00:27:09,750
You are not even smart!

348
00:27:09,750 --> 00:27:14,010
What? What did you say?

349
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:18,280
What's going on? What happened?

350
00:27:18,280 --> 00:27:21,510
Ms. Park, what education are you providing to the children?

351
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:26,240
Teach Se Chan how to treat his younger brother first.

352
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:32,340
And make sure he never hits Se Jong ever again.

353
00:27:58,900 --> 00:28:04,770
It's a robot you worked hard on for hours to make.

354
00:28:04,770 --> 00:28:09,820
But you're upset because it broke in a second, aren't you?

355
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:15,950
I'm very good at putting together a robot.

356
00:28:15,950 --> 00:28:19,850
Do you want to do it again with me?

357
00:28:19,850 --> 00:28:24,750
No, please throw that robot away for me.

358
00:28:31,820 --> 00:28:35,290
Chief Jo.

359
00:28:35,290 --> 00:28:39,120
Actually,

360
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:42,680
I did wrong.

361
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:48,460
Hyung told me not to touch it.

362
00:28:48,460 --> 00:28:53,460
But I did and broke it.

363
00:28:53,460 --> 00:28:58,190
I will go and say I'm sorry.

364
00:28:58,190 --> 00:29:00,120
Se Jong.

365
00:29:00,120 --> 00:29:02,950
This is your brother's fault.

366
00:29:02,950 --> 00:29:06,260
It was just a mistake that you dropped the toy.

367
00:29:06,260 --> 00:29:10,250
But it's his fault that he hit you.

368
00:29:10,250 --> 00:29:13,910
So, you don't have to feel sorry.

369
00:29:13,910 --> 00:29:18,300
What did I say you would be when you grew up?

370
00:29:18,300 --> 00:29:20,770
A great person.

371
00:29:20,770 --> 00:29:25,150
That's right. Se Jong will take over from your father

372
00:29:25,150 --> 00:29:28,900
and become the leader of the FT Group.

373
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:33,420
Such a great person does not have to bow down to just anyone.

374
00:29:33,420 --> 00:29:36,360
Do you understand?

375
00:29:51,620 --> 00:29:54,780
Is Se Jong okay?

376
00:29:54,780 --> 00:29:57,770
He's calmed down now.

377
00:29:59,070 --> 00:30:01,460
Chief Jo.

378
00:30:01,460 --> 00:30:02,980
Yes?

379
00:30:02,980 --> 00:30:08,660
Then can you calm down Se Chan as well?

380
00:30:08,660 --> 00:30:10,670
What do you mean?

381
00:30:10,670 --> 00:30:15,660
You were very harsh to Se Chan earlier.

382
00:30:15,660 --> 00:30:17,730
My goodness.

383
00:30:17,730 --> 00:30:19,410
What did you say?

384
00:30:19,410 --> 00:30:21,940
I know Se Chan was wrong

385
00:30:21,940 --> 00:30:25,930
to get angry with Se Jong and hit him on the head.

386
00:30:25,930 --> 00:30:31,620
But without knowing the details, you got angry only with Se Chan.

387
00:30:31,620 --> 00:30:35,920
And you even said he's not smart.

388
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:38,830
I get that you might have said that because you were too surprised--

389
00:30:38,830 --> 00:30:42,060
What are you saying to me, Ms. Park?

390
00:30:42,060 --> 00:30:46,590
Are you trying to teach me as well? How dare you try to teach me!

391
00:30:46,590 --> 00:30:48,590
That's not it. What I'm saying is,

392
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:52,950
when there is a conflict, you have to listen to both sides of the story

393
00:30:52,950 --> 00:30:55,730
and decide fairly based on the facts.

394
00:30:55,730 --> 00:30:59,120
But Se Chan's feelings got hurt a lot.

395
00:30:59,120 --> 00:31:01,590
Look here, Ms. Park!

396
00:31:01,590 --> 00:31:05,440
Se Jong is a kindergartner and much younger than Se Chan.

397
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:09,980
And Se Chan hit someone so much younger than him. Are you saying that's okay?

398
00:31:09,980 --> 00:31:12,610
Shouldn't you stop Se Chan from hitting Se Jong again

399
00:31:12,610 --> 00:31:15,610
by disciplining and punishing him clearly?

400
00:31:15,610 --> 00:31:19,160
Instead of what? You want me to console Se Chan?

401
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:22,500
Please conduct your education properly.

402
00:31:22,500 --> 00:31:25,470
If something like this happens again,

403
00:31:25,470 --> 00:31:30,350
you will be held responsible as well.

404
00:31:39,470 --> 00:31:42,590
It's raining.

405
00:31:42,630 --> 00:31:46,250
But why is the sound of rain so loud?

406
00:31:46,250 --> 00:31:50,620
Why is it raining so much when it's winter?

407
00:31:50,620 --> 00:31:52,660
Next, we will have regional weather reports.

408
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:57,710
In Seoul and Gyeonggi Province right now is very cloudy and started to rain harshly.

409
00:31:57,710 --> 00:32:00,340
It's going to lead to heavy rain overnight.

410
00:32:00,340 --> 00:32:03,250
Please be careful of potential floods and landslides.

411
00:32:03,250 --> 00:32:04,920
The reason for the heavy rain tonight is

412
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:09,910
- Flood and landslide?
 - due to the clouds forming above the ocean in the west coming to the capital area.

413
00:32:09,930 --> 00:32:12,990
What about my gold?

414
00:32:12,990 --> 00:32:16,910
What if they wash away in the rain?

415
00:32:18,310 --> 00:32:23,350
Oh, my goodness!

416
00:32:23,350 --> 00:32:28,430
Why is it raining this heavily today?

417
00:32:30,370 --> 00:32:34,740
This is so annoying.

418
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:47,140
Oh, my babies!

419
00:32:47,140 --> 00:32:50,560
You've come back!

420
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:53,870
Oh, my babies!

421
00:32:55,750 --> 00:32:57,990
What? What is it?

422
00:32:57,990 --> 00:32:59,950
Where did it go?

423
00:32:59,950 --> 00:33:01,940
It was right here. Where did it all go?

424
00:33:01,940 --> 00:33:05,450
Where did my golds go?

425
00:33:08,630 --> 00:33:11,380
You were here! My pretty babies.

426
00:33:11,380 --> 00:33:15,380
Oh, my babies!

427
00:33:17,580 --> 00:33:19,590
What happened? My golds!

428
00:33:19,590 --> 00:33:23,350
Where did they go? Why are they keep disappearing!

429
00:33:23,350 --> 00:33:28,400
My golds! Where did you go, my babies?

430
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:32,220
My babies! Please don't go!

431
00:33:32,220 --> 00:33:37,090
Don't go. Don't go!

432
00:33:37,090 --> 00:33:40,230
It was a dream.

433
00:33:40,230 --> 00:33:46,300
But why are my golds keep running away?

434
00:33:46,300 --> 00:33:48,700
Could it be that they are not

435
00:33:48,700 --> 00:33:50,950
in Young Gook's safe in his study?

436
00:33:50,950 --> 00:33:54,370
Are they somewhere else?

437
00:33:54,370 --> 00:33:57,650
No, no, no. Where would they go?

438
00:33:57,650 --> 00:34:03,370
Right, right. They must be in Young Gook's study.

439
00:34:03,370 --> 00:34:05,760
Of course, yes.

440
00:34:14,340 --> 00:34:18,950
[We buy and sell gold]

441
00:34:27,910 --> 00:34:33,670
[Baruni Jewelry and Gold dealer]
