You are pretty.

511
00:40:05,850 --> 00:40:10,970
Then, should we start dating?

512
00:40:10,970 --> 00:40:13,740
What?

513
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:26,900
[Fantom]

514
00:40:26,900 --> 00:40:30,530
Sister-in-law?

515
00:40:30,530 --> 00:40:34,400
Were you waiting to see me?

516
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:37,320
Pardon? Yes.

517
00:40:37,320 --> 00:40:39,980
Why didn't you go inside and wait outside?

518
00:40:39,980 --> 00:40:44,460
It's not like you came to see a stranger.

519
00:40:44,460 --> 00:40:50,280
Sister-in-law, what's going on? Did something happen?

520
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:53,180
Sister-in-law...

521
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:55,170
What?

522
00:40:55,170 --> 00:40:57,620
Soo Chul lost his job?

523
00:40:57,620 --> 00:40:59,630
Yes.

524
00:40:59,630 --> 00:41:01,680
What do we do now?

525
00:41:01,680 --> 00:41:07,860
Our family has been living on the wages he brings in.

526
00:41:07,860 --> 00:41:12,130
I don't know how we're going to live from now on.

527
00:41:12,130 --> 00:41:16,380
I've looked everywhere trying to get a job.

528
00:41:16,380 --> 00:41:22,550
But there was no place willing to hire a housewife like me.

529
00:41:22,560 --> 00:41:28,120
That's why I've come here, despite shame and embarrassment.

530
00:41:28,120 --> 00:41:32,400
Sister-in-law, can't you please hire me as a cleaner in this store?

531
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:35,200
Please let me work here, Sister-in-law.

532
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:40,470
Sister-in-law, what are you saying? Why would you work here?

533
00:41:40,470 --> 00:41:46,000
I have to work at least for us to survive.

534
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:51,520
I'll help you out until Soo Chul finds a new job.

535
00:41:51,520 --> 00:41:53,810
No, please don't do that.

536
00:41:53,810 --> 00:41:56,870
If Soo Chul finds that out, he will flip.

537
00:41:56,870 --> 00:42:02,240
He even refused to live in your apartment.

538
00:42:06,870 --> 00:42:10,320
No, I can't take it.

539
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:13,930
Just don't let Soo Chul know.

540
00:42:13,930 --> 00:42:17,860
Use it for living expenses and endure for a while.

541
00:42:17,860 --> 00:42:22,970
Soo Chul is healthy and hard working. He will find something soon.

542
00:42:22,970 --> 00:42:25,220
Until he does,

543
00:42:25,220 --> 00:42:31,130
I will help you with living expenses every month for a while, so don't worry.

544
00:42:31,130 --> 00:42:33,650
Sister-in-law...

545
00:42:33,650 --> 00:42:37,760
How will I pay you back for this gratitude?

546
00:42:37,760 --> 00:42:40,510
You don't have to think about finding a job somewhere.

547
00:42:40,510 --> 00:42:44,570
Please take care of our Soo Chul and do not let his pride suffer.

548
00:42:44,570 --> 00:42:51,950
He will be going through the hardest time, having lost the job. Please comfort him a lot.

549
00:42:51,950 --> 00:42:53,640
Yes, Sister-in-law.

550
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:54,970
Don't worry about it.

551
00:42:54,970 --> 00:42:59,970
- Please put it in your bag.
- Okay.

552
00:43:16,320 --> 00:43:20,620
How much is this?

553
00:43:20,620 --> 00:43:22,690
Three million won?

554
00:43:22,690 --> 00:43:26,210
She gave me a lot of money!

555
00:43:26,210 --> 00:43:31,870
Is she going to give this much every month until Soo Chul gets a job?

556
00:43:31,870 --> 00:43:34,620
Oh, my goodness!

557
00:43:34,620 --> 00:43:42,060
I live in luxury, thanks to Soo Chul's wealthy sister.

558
00:43:46,280 --> 00:43:48,850
CEO Anna!

559
00:43:48,850 --> 00:43:50,440
Ms. Park.

560
00:43:50,440 --> 00:43:53,460
Please don't run. You might fall!

561
00:43:53,460 --> 00:43:56,890
I'm so excited and happy to see you.

562
00:43:56,890 --> 00:43:58,890
Was it not difficult to find here?

563
00:43:58,890 --> 00:44:01,240
I said I would come and pick you up.

564
00:44:01,240 --> 00:44:03,840
I'm not a child.

565
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:06,740
It's easy getting here on the bus.

566
00:44:06,740 --> 00:44:10,370
Maybe I thought of you as a young child.

567
00:44:10,370 --> 00:44:15,650
I've been worried after leaving you all alone. Have you been well?

568
00:44:15,650 --> 00:44:18,340
Has anything happened?

569
00:44:18,340 --> 00:44:20,370
No, CEO Anna.

570
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:25,460
Let's go. I've made a reservation. Let's eat and talk.

571
00:44:25,460 --> 00:44:27,460
Yes.

572
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:31,890
Dad!

573
00:44:31,890 --> 00:44:34,980
Dan Dan.

574
00:44:34,980 --> 00:44:36,780
Hello.

575
00:44:36,780 --> 00:44:39,340
Yes, hello, CEO Anna.

576
00:44:39,340 --> 00:44:43,020
What are you doing here, Dan Dan?

577
00:44:43,020 --> 00:44:47,540
I wanted to buy Ms. Park a meal, so I asked for a date.

578
00:44:47,540 --> 00:44:49,970
I suddenly left Chairman Lee's house,

579
00:44:49,970 --> 00:44:53,280
so I didn't have time to say a proper goodbye to her.

580
00:44:53,280 --> 00:44:57,370
I see. Thank you.

581
00:44:57,370 --> 00:45:03,350
Driver Park, since we are all here, why don't you join us?

582
00:45:03,350 --> 00:45:05,580
No, thank you. I'm okay.

583
00:45:05,580 --> 00:45:09,020
Dan Dan, please go ahead with the CEO.

584
00:45:09,020 --> 00:45:12,400
No, please do join us.

585
00:45:17,700 --> 00:45:20,590
I heard this place was good, so I made a reservation here. What do you think?

586
00:45:20,590 --> 00:45:22,570
Do the steaks taste okay?

587
00:45:22,570 --> 00:45:24,620
Yes.

588
00:45:25,970 --> 00:45:29,350
Yes, it's delicious. It melts in the mouth.

589
00:45:29,350 --> 00:45:31,800
Eat as much as you want, Ms. Park.

590
00:45:31,800 --> 00:45:34,680
I will bring you here often.

591
00:45:34,680 --> 00:45:38,970
Really? Thank you.

592
00:45:42,290 --> 00:45:46,330
Since having steak in a nice restaurant like this in a while,

593
00:45:46,330 --> 00:45:49,110
it reminds me of a teary steak I had before.

594
00:45:49,110 --> 00:45:52,490
Teary steak?

595
00:45:52,490 --> 00:45:54,350
What is that?

596
00:45:54,350 --> 00:45:56,230
While I was in university,

597
00:45:56,230 --> 00:45:59,800
a guy I met on my first blind date took me to a nice restaurant.

598
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:02,460
When did you go on a blind date?

599
00:46:02,460 --> 00:46:06,730
Dad! Did you think I never went on a blind date?

600
00:46:06,730 --> 00:46:10,210
And? You went to the restaurant, and then?

601
00:46:10,210 --> 00:46:14,310
I said, let's just have pasta, which was cheaper,

602
00:46:14,310 --> 00:46:19,500
but I guess he liked me, so he wanted to treat me to a steak.

603
00:46:19,500 --> 00:46:24,390
So he ordered a steak and tried to cut it for me.

604
00:46:24,390 --> 00:46:30,340
And while he was cutting, perhaps because I looked so pretty,

605
00:46:30,340 --> 00:46:34,300
his hands were shaking like this.

606
00:46:34,300 --> 00:46:36,080
His hands were shaking this much!

607
00:46:36,080 --> 00:46:40,480
But then, the steak flew away.

608
00:46:40,480 --> 00:46:42,310
Oh, no! Really?

609
00:46:42,310 --> 00:46:46,720
We were poor students, so we didn't want to throw it away.

610
00:46:46,720 --> 00:46:51,120
So I said, let's just pick it up and wash it and eat it.

611
00:46:51,120 --> 00:46:53,940
Oh, no! How could you do that?

612
00:46:53,940 --> 00:46:55,810
- Is it a true story?
- Yes!

613
00:46:55,810 --> 00:46:59,300
But, the restaurant owner felt sorry for us,

614
00:46:59,300 --> 00:47:04,870
so he made us a new one. It's a funny memory now.

615
00:47:23,560 --> 00:47:27,270
Thank you for today, CEO Anna. I really enjoyed it.

616
00:47:27,270 --> 00:47:29,220
Me, too.

617
00:47:29,220 --> 00:47:34,440
I've relied on you a lot all this time. So it was good to see you again.

618
00:47:34,440 --> 00:47:36,770
Thank you for everything.

619
00:47:36,770 --> 00:47:41,540
What do you mean? I'm the one who's grateful.

620
00:47:41,540 --> 00:47:43,090
I will see you again, Ms. Park.

621
00:47:43,090 --> 00:47:47,140
Yes. Goodbye, CEO Anna.

622
00:47:50,710 --> 00:47:55,170
Dad, what did it mean that CEO Anna just said?

623
00:47:55,170 --> 00:47:59,810
Did you quit your job there?

624
00:47:59,810 --> 00:48:05,300
What? Oh.

625
00:48:16,260 --> 00:48:20,970
I was so happy just being with them.

626
00:48:20,970 --> 00:48:24,170
Just sharing a meal makes me so happy.

627
00:48:24,170 --> 00:48:26,280
His hands were shaking this much!

628
00:48:26,280 --> 00:48:32,700
Is it possible to put everything back the way it was?

629
00:48:35,220 --> 00:48:37,740
Hyung, can you pass it to me?

630
00:48:37,740 --> 00:48:40,460
Let me play just once.

631
00:48:47,740 --> 00:48:50,360
Se Jong, are you okay?

632
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:53,890
Se Jong! Oh, my goodness!

633
00:48:53,890 --> 00:48:56,710
What do we do? What do we do?

634
00:48:56,710 --> 00:48:59,860
Your nose is bleeding! What should we do?

635
00:48:59,860 --> 00:49:02,140
My goodness!

636
00:49:02,140 --> 00:49:06,060
Lee Se Chan! What did you do to my Se Jong?

637
00:49:06,060 --> 00:49:09,350
Why are you acting like this? Why are you so mean!

638
00:49:09,350 --> 00:49:13,010
Who do you take after!

639
00:49:13,010 --> 00:49:16,320
No, I didn't. I didn't do it!

640
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:20,100
Oh my, look at him lying! Don't you know that lying is the worst?

641
00:49:20,100 --> 00:49:24,090
Where did you learn something so terrible?

642
00:49:24,090 --> 00:49:27,200
Chief Jo, what are you doing?

643
00:49:27,200 --> 00:49:33,200
Lee Se Chan, if you do this to my Se Jong one more time, we'll see what will happen!

644
00:49:33,230 --> 00:49:35,810
Chief Jo.

645
00:49:35,810 --> 00:49:38,810
Why are you being like that to my older brother?

646
00:49:38,810 --> 00:49:42,680
He didn't do it on purpose.

647
00:49:42,680 --> 00:49:45,310
I fell on my own.

648
00:49:45,310 --> 00:49:47,780
My goodness.

649
00:49:56,530 --> 00:50:03,110
Ms. Park. Why does Chief Jo only hate me so much?

650
00:50:03,110 --> 00:50:06,320
Am I really such a terrible child?

651
00:50:06,320 --> 00:50:08,770
No, you are not, Se Chan. Absolutely not.

652
00:50:08,770 --> 00:50:13,000
Why does Chief Jo blame me all the time?

653
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:15,820
I really hate Chief Jo!

654
00:50:15,820 --> 00:50:18,830
I really hate her!

655
00:50:27,300 --> 00:50:29,040
What do you want to talk about?

656
00:50:29,040 --> 00:50:32,710
Chief Jo, you went overboard.

657
00:50:32,710 --> 00:50:34,410
What?

658
00:50:34,410 --> 00:50:40,480
I saw it when I was coming home. Se Chan and Se Jong fell together while chasing the ball.

659
00:50:40,480 --> 00:50:43,480
Se Chan didn't push Se Jong to fall.

660
00:50:43,480 --> 00:50:48,320
But how can you not even listen to their stories and even hit him?

661
00:50:48,320 --> 00:50:50,280
What? When did I hit him?

662
00:50:50,280 --> 00:50:55,240
How can you say such a terrible thing to me? I'm going to be the madam of this house--

663
00:50:55,240 --> 00:51:00,740
As a person who's going to become their mother, I disciplined Se Chan. That's all.

664
00:51:00,740 --> 00:51:03,330
If he did something wrong, he should be disciplined.

665
00:51:03,330 --> 00:51:06,890
Then you should listen to the kids first and scold them if they did something wrong.

666
00:51:06,890 --> 00:51:11,630
And even if they did wrong, I don't believe you should hit the child.

667
00:51:11,630 --> 00:51:14,080
What are you trying to do with me, Ms. Park?

668
00:51:14,080 --> 00:51:17,010
I'm going to be the madam of this house!

669
00:51:17,010 --> 00:51:19,760
How dare you talk to me with your eyes glaring like that?

670
00:51:19,760 --> 00:51:23,480
Why don't you know your places?

671
00:51:27,450 --> 00:51:29,800
What is going on with you two?

672
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:31,700
Are you fighting?

673
00:51:31,700 --> 00:51:36,840
Chairman, what do you mean? Why would we fight?

674
00:51:36,840 --> 00:51:40,150
It's nothing, so please don't pay attention.

675
00:51:40,150 --> 00:51:41,980
No, Chief Jo Noona.

676
00:51:41,980 --> 00:51:45,960
It sounded like Ms. Park was telling you off.

677
00:51:45,960 --> 00:51:50,520
I need to hear from Ms. Park Noona for what's the reason.

678
00:51:50,520 --> 00:51:52,710
What's going on?

679
00:51:52,710 --> 00:51:56,880
Yes, Chairman. It's something you ought to know.

680
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:59,580
Ms. Park. Please stop.

681
00:51:59,580 --> 00:52:02,210
No, it's about the Chairman's children.

682
00:52:02,210 --> 00:52:04,630
He, more than anyone, should know.

683
00:52:04,630 --> 00:52:09,340
There's no reason for the Chairman to worry about it.

684
00:52:09,340 --> 00:52:13,150
Yes, please. I need to know if it's about my children.

685
00:52:13,150 --> 00:52:15,970
Please tell me.

686
00:52:15,970 --> 00:52:21,690
Yesterday, Se Jong mistakenly broke a toy that Se Chan put together after two hours of hard work.

687
00:52:21,690 --> 00:52:24,200
So Se Chan hit Se Jong on the head.

688
00:52:24,200 --> 00:52:30,110
But without listening to their stories, Chief Jo scolded Se Chan only.

689
00:52:30,110 --> 00:52:35,420
She was even saying very hurtful things to him while doing so.

690
00:52:35,420 --> 00:52:37,020
That is...

691
00:52:37,020 --> 00:52:41,710
And just now, Se Jong and Se Chan fell at the same time while playing with a ball.

692
00:52:41,710 --> 00:52:44,290
And that caused Se Jong a nose bleed.

693
00:52:44,290 --> 00:52:51,240
Se Chan did not cause Se Jong to fall, but Chief Jo suddenly hit Se Chan.

694
00:52:51,240 --> 00:52:54,060
Ms. Park!

695
00:52:54,090 --> 00:52:55,860
Did she hit Se Chan?

696
00:52:55,860 --> 00:53:02,530
Yes. Why would Chief Jo not listen to the kids' stories and only scold Se Chan all the time?

697
00:53:02,530 --> 00:53:06,930
I believe that is wrong.

698
00:53:06,930 --> 00:53:10,430
Children know when they are treated differently.

699
00:53:10,430 --> 00:53:15,130
The discriminative treatment hurts their feelings and is not good for their emotional development.

700
00:53:15,130 --> 00:53:23,450
And, no matter the reason, violence is bad.

701
00:53:23,450 --> 00:53:27,780
Ms. Park, what do you mean by violence? How can you put it that way?

702
00:53:27,780 --> 00:53:32,000
I was shocked to see Se Jong's nose bleed, so I gently pushed Se Chan.

703
00:53:32,000 --> 00:53:34,930
Chief Jo! Why are you lying?

704
00:53:34,930 --> 00:53:38,010
You absolutely hit Se Chan!

705
00:53:38,010 --> 00:53:42,180
Please stop both of you.

706
00:53:42,220 --> 00:53:44,860
That's enough.

707
00:53:50,000 --> 00:53:51,800
Yes, that's right.

708
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:55,950
Chief Jo hit me on the back.

709
00:53:55,950 --> 00:53:57,880
Really?

710
00:53:57,880 --> 00:54:01,050
Chief Jo only scolds me every day.

711
00:54:01,050 --> 00:54:05,930
I don't know why she likes Se Jong and dislikes me always.

712
00:54:05,930 --> 00:54:11,150
I think Chief Jo hates me.

713
00:54:11,150 --> 00:54:14,370
I don't think that's it.

714
00:54:14,370 --> 00:54:19,100
It's because Se Jong is very young, that's why.

715
00:54:19,100 --> 00:54:22,740
But Chief Jo definitely did wrong with this.

716
00:54:22,740 --> 00:54:28,490
I will make sure something like this never happens again.

717
00:54:28,490 --> 00:54:32,460
So don't cry, Se Chan.

718
00:54:38,450 --> 00:54:45,880
Chief Jo Noona, no matter what wrong behavior the children do, please don't hit them.

719
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:50,270
If you scold them and hit them, they will go sideways.

720
00:54:50,270 --> 00:54:56,620
My middle school friend, Byung Cheol, ran away from his house for that reason and couldn't even finish middle school.

721
00:54:56,620 --> 00:55:04,180
Have you not heard the phrase don't even hit the child with a flower?

722
00:55:04,180 --> 00:55:08,390
Even if you are the one I'm supposed to marry,

723
00:55:08,390 --> 00:55:13,940
I won't tolerate you treating my young children like that.

724
00:55:21,410 --> 00:55:24,890
Chief Jo Noona!

725
00:55:39,590 --> 00:55:42,550
Chief Jo Noona!

726
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:51,320
The call cannot be connected.

727
00:55:51,320 --> 00:55:54,160
I think she's really upset.

728
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:56,830
Was I too harsh?

729
00:55:56,830 --> 00:56:02,500
No, I wasn't. Chief Jo Noona was clearly wrong this time.

730
00:56:04,470 --> 00:56:08,080
This is why 41-year-old Lee Young Gook delayed his wedding.

731
00:56:08,080 --> 00:56:12,000
Why is everything complicated and difficult?

732
00:56:14,560 --> 00:56:17,430
Auntie, a bottle of soju and some pork skin, please.

733
00:56:17,430 --> 00:56:19,680
Okay!

734
00:56:21,960 --> 00:56:27,250
I mean, even if he's a stupid 22-year-old,

735
00:56:27,250 --> 00:56:31,950
how can he crush me in front of Ms. Park?

736
00:56:31,950 --> 00:56:38,060
Seriously. What should I do with that wench, Ms. Park?

737
00:56:49,250 --> 00:56:52,600
- Wait a minute. I will bring it.
- Yes.

738
00:56:52,600 --> 00:56:56,300
You came here today. Sokcho night beach lady.

739
00:57:00,310 --> 00:57:05,470
Ajussi, do you know me?

740
00:57:05,470 --> 00:57:07,450
Pardon?

741
00:57:07,450 --> 00:57:11,090
Who do you think you are to sit in front of me?

742
00:57:11,090 --> 00:57:15,000
What kind of joke is that?

743
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:16,820
It's me!

744
00:57:16,820 --> 00:57:19,910
The cute teddy bear.

745
00:57:21,350 --> 00:57:26,340
Look here, Ajussi. We don't know each other's names or anything.

746
00:57:26,340 --> 00:57:31,500
So why do you think it's okay for you to sit here without my permission?

747
00:57:31,500 --> 00:57:36,530
You are not mistaken about anything, are you?

748
00:57:38,860 --> 00:57:42,790
No, I'm not mistaken.

749
00:57:42,790 --> 00:57:47,470
If I offended you, I'm sorry.

750
00:57:47,470 --> 00:57:51,300
Ajussi, I am getting married.

751
00:57:51,300 --> 00:57:54,310
From now on, please pretend you don't know me even if you see me.

752
00:57:54,310 --> 00:57:57,140
You know what it means, right?

753
00:57:57,140 --> 00:58:01,630
We don't know each other.

754
00:58:06,400 --> 00:58:12,920
Yes, I understand clearly. I won't show that I know you so please don't worry.

755
00:58:12,920 --> 00:58:18,970
And, congratulations on getting married.

756
00:58:18,970 --> 00:58:22,800
I mean it. Congratulations.

757
00:58:44,410 --> 00:58:49,880
That's right. How did I get here after all?

758
00:59:05,090 --> 00:59:08,040
What would have happened to Se Chan if I weren't there?

759
00:59:08,040 --> 00:59:11,320
And even if Se Jong is very young.

760
00:59:11,320 --> 00:59:14,750
Why does she discriminate against Se Chan like that?

761
00:59:14,750 --> 00:59:17,410
It hurts his feelings.

762
00:59:18,750 --> 00:59:24,140
For the sake of our Jenny, Se Chan, and Se Jong,

763
00:59:24,140 --> 00:59:26,640
I will have to stay in this house.

764
00:59:26,640 --> 00:59:29,440
I will protect the children.

765
00:59:29,440 --> 00:59:33,500
Right, I will not leave no matter what.

766
00:59:38,090 --> 00:59:40,600
Ms. Park Noona.

767
00:59:40,610 --> 00:59:45,320
- Chairman.
- What are you doing here?

768
00:59:45,320 --> 00:59:51,110
Well, I was feeling a bit frustrated.

769
00:59:52,460 --> 00:59:54,950
I came out because I felt the same.

770
00:59:54,950 --> 00:59:57,060
Let's have a drink together.

771
00:59:57,060 --> 00:59:59,550
Please sit.

772
01:00:12,230 --> 01:00:15,940
Ms. Park Noona. I want to thank you for earlier.

773
01:00:15,940 --> 01:00:21,410
I think Se Chan feels better because of you.

774
01:00:21,410 --> 01:00:27,750
Even still, he is probably very upset.

775
01:00:27,750 --> 01:00:33,020
From what I see, because you treat the kids fairly and truthfully,

776
01:00:33,020 --> 01:00:36,320
the children like you.

777
01:00:36,320 --> 01:00:40,150
What is this? Is he complimenting me?

778
01:00:40,150 --> 01:00:42,270
What's up?

779
01:00:42,270 --> 01:00:46,010
What I am saying is I feel I can trust you.

780
01:00:46,010 --> 01:00:51,010
And that I feel secure that you are in our house.

781
01:00:51,010 --> 01:00:54,810
Please take good care of our children in the future as well.

782
01:00:54,810 --> 01:00:58,460
Yes, I will.

783
01:01:05,740 --> 01:01:08,920
We should have done this a lot earlier.

784
01:01:08,920 --> 01:01:13,210
Let's get along well from now on as well, as a member of the same house.

785
01:01:13,210 --> 01:01:15,560
Yes.

786
01:01:27,480 --> 01:01:32,350
What's wrong?

787
01:01:35,220 --> 01:01:38,100
That is...

788
01:01:38,100 --> 01:01:41,520
I just remembered that I was doing cheers with beers

789
01:01:41,520 --> 01:01:46,490
with someone here, just like we did now.

790
01:01:48,970 --> 01:01:50,300
Oh, sure, you did!

791
01:01:50,300 --> 01:01:54,180
Do you think you did cheers with a handful of people here?

792
01:01:54,180 --> 01:01:57,100
Excuse me first.

793
01:01:59,130 --> 01:02:02,510
Why does she leave in the middle of drinking?

794
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:06,410
Ms. Park Noona has no manners.

795
01:02:06,450 --> 01:02:09,550
We don't hit off that well.

796
01:02:30,160 --> 01:02:33,050
Chief Jo Noona.

797
01:02:33,050 --> 01:02:35,030
Chairman, earlier today--

798
01:02:35,030 --> 01:02:38,620
No, let me say it first.

799
01:02:38,620 --> 01:02:42,420
I am sorry about earlier.

800
01:02:42,420 --> 01:02:46,140
No, Chairman. I'm the one who's sorry.

801
01:02:46,140 --> 01:02:49,740
I should've thought about it more.

802
01:02:49,740 --> 01:02:55,310
Se Jong is a baby who needs hands-on guidance from adults.

803
01:02:55,310 --> 01:03:01,480
Also, I almost raised Se Jong myself.

804
01:03:01,480 --> 01:03:04,250
I think I was overprotective about him without realizing it.

805
01:03:04,250 --> 01:03:09,940
I'm sorry. I overreacted to Se Chan as well.

806
01:03:09,940 --> 01:03:13,580
I was too harsh to you as well.

807
01:03:13,580 --> 01:03:16,820
I'm sorry. I want to apologize.

808
01:03:16,820 --> 01:03:21,850
So please don't be angry.

809
01:03:21,850 --> 01:03:26,590
You are not angry anymore, are you?

810
01:03:41,610 --> 01:03:42,960
I have a call.

811
01:03:42,960 --> 01:03:47,090
It's from Jung Woo. Koh Jung Woo. One moment, please.

812
01:03:47,090 --> 01:03:49,050
Yes, it's me.

813
01:03:49,050 --> 01:03:52,870
Young Gook, I need you to come to the office tomorrow.

814
01:03:52,870 --> 01:03:56,250
What? To the office?

815
01:03:56,250 --> 01:03:59,630
Am I not on sick leave?

816
01:03:59,630 --> 01:04:01,690
Okay, I get it. I'll be there tomorrow.

817
01:04:01,690 --> 01:04:04,570
I will see you then.

818
01:04:04,600 --> 01:04:06,200
Why to the office?

819
01:04:06,200 --> 01:04:11,050
Isn't Executive Director Han taking good care of everything? Is something wrong?

820
01:04:11,050 --> 01:04:15,060
It's not that. If you vacate the Chairman's office for too long, rumors might go around.

821
01:04:15,060 --> 01:04:18,490
Rumors like whether the Chairman is alive or dead. And it might affect the company's stock price.

822
01:04:18,490 --> 01:04:21,220
Whether the company is going bankrupt or not and calling an emergency Directors' meeting

823
01:04:21,220 --> 01:04:26,130
to choose a new Chairman, it can go crazy like that.

824
01:04:26,130 --> 01:04:31,930
Chairman. Did your memory come back all of a sudden?

825
01:04:31,930 --> 01:04:37,540
I feel like you've gone back to your original state.

826
01:04:37,590 --> 01:04:43,110
I've been going to the office with my father since I was seven and got trained in business management.

827
01:04:43,110 --> 01:04:48,340
Chairman. You are amazing.

828
01:04:48,340 --> 01:04:51,870
Even so, please come with me tomorrow.

829
01:04:51,870 --> 01:04:56,600
Jung Woo tells me to say nothing and just come by, but I shouldn't make mistakes.

830
01:04:56,600 --> 01:05:00,680
My memory loss must not be revealed for a while.

831
01:05:00,680 --> 01:05:03,190
I get it. I will come with you.

832
01:05:03,190 --> 01:05:05,290
I told you already.

833
01:05:05,290 --> 01:05:09,510
I will always be by your side.

834
01:05:39,080 --> 01:05:40,770
Hello, Executive Director Han.

835
01:05:40,770 --> 01:05:43,050
Welcome, Chairman.

836
01:05:43,050 --> 01:05:48,610
Executive Director Han, how come you turned into a grandpa?

837
01:05:51,090 --> 01:05:54,930
Young Gook, you agreed not to say something like that.

838
01:05:54,930 --> 01:05:57,340
Ah, right.

839
01:05:57,340 --> 01:06:00,990
Chief Jo Noona. I shouldn't say anything today.

840
01:06:00,990 --> 01:06:04,830
Please pinch my back every time I open my mouth.

841
01:06:06,460 --> 01:06:08,500
I was joking. It was a joke.

842
01:06:08,500 --> 01:06:10,760
I haven't gone that far yet.

843
01:06:10,760 --> 01:06:15,110
Chairman, please just follow me.

844
01:06:15,110 --> 01:06:17,610
Let's go.

845
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:29,610
Now, the new madam of this company is me.

846
01:06:33,450 --> 01:06:34,950
Hello, sir.

847
01:06:34,950 --> 01:06:37,980
Yes, thank you for your hard work.

848
01:06:37,980 --> 01:06:40,850
Young Gook, just greet people with your eyes.

849
01:06:40,850 --> 01:06:43,530
Ah, really?

850
01:06:46,970 --> 01:06:52,190
We've put off the merger until your memory returns.

851
01:06:52,190 --> 01:06:56,700
And I'm managing the projects that were underway.

852
01:06:56,700 --> 01:07:01,470
Chairman, please take a look at them when you have time.

853
01:07:09,020 --> 01:07:13,570
Executive Director Han, please take good care of things until my memory comes back.

854
01:07:13,570 --> 01:07:16,390
I will take these home to study.

855
01:07:16,390 --> 01:07:21,470
Yes, Chairman. Excuse me first since I have a meeting.

856
01:07:24,190 --> 01:07:28,400
Executive Director Han! Fighting!

857
01:07:28,400 --> 01:07:30,750
Fighting!

858
01:07:35,020 --> 01:07:37,670
It's so suffocating.

859
01:07:37,670 --> 01:07:42,040
I thought I'd die from wearing the tie.

860
01:07:42,060 --> 01:07:48,590
Jung Woo, what will happen to my father's company if my memory never comes back?

861
01:07:48,590 --> 01:07:52,480
Do you really not remember anything?

862
01:07:52,480 --> 01:07:54,520
Nothing at all?

863
01:07:54,520 --> 01:07:58,660
I think it was the moment the accident happened,

864
01:07:58,660 --> 01:08:02,190
but I only remember the moment rolling down the mountain trying to catch a handkerchief flying away,

865
01:08:02,190 --> 01:08:04,470
and drinking a beer with someone at the convenience store.

866
01:08:04,470 --> 01:08:08,660
I think I remember a bit, but it's all mixed up.

867
01:08:08,660 --> 01:08:10,670
Really?

868
01:08:10,670 --> 01:08:15,410
I think your memory will come back at some point if it keeps going like that.

869
01:08:15,410 --> 01:08:19,500
Right, I really hope so.

870
01:08:19,500 --> 01:08:23,290
Right, can you clear your schedule for Christmas Eve?

871
01:08:23,290 --> 01:08:26,010
Christmas Eve? Why?

872
01:08:26,010 --> 01:08:29,260
On that day, I'm going to get married.

873
01:08:29,260 --> 01:08:33,180
What? Are you getting married?

874
01:08:33,180 --> 01:08:34,670
To whom?

875
01:08:34,670 --> 01:08:38,210
What do you mean, to whom? To Chief Jo Noona.

876
01:08:38,210 --> 01:08:41,770
I heard I was in a relationship with her before I lost my memory.

877
01:08:41,770 --> 01:08:44,080
I heard that we promised to get married before this year passed.

878
01:08:44,080 --> 01:08:45,720
What?

879
01:08:45,720 --> 01:08:49,320
You and Chief Jo were going to get married?

880
01:08:49,320 --> 01:08:52,070
Why are you so surprised? You didn't know?

881
01:08:52,070 --> 01:08:54,180
Of course, I'm surprised.

882
01:08:54,180 --> 01:08:59,560
Let alone getting married, but I've never heard of you dating each other.

883
01:08:59,560 --> 01:09:05,280
You told me that you were dating someone with a huge age gap.

884
01:09:05,280 --> 01:09:07,600
What?

885
01:09:09,280 --> 01:09:12,310
Was I dating someone much older?

886
01:09:12,310 --> 01:09:14,390
No, it's not that.

887
01:09:14,390 --> 01:09:20,650
You were dating a young lady who was much younger than you.

888
01:09:20,650 --> 01:09:27,390
Was I dating a young lady much younger than me?

889
01:09:35,840 --> 01:09:42,780
 A smile blooms in every step 

890
01:09:42,780 --> 01:09:47,500
 It's a shiny day because of you 

891
01:09:47,500 --> 01:09:49,590
 It's sunshine day 

892
01:09:49,590 --> 01:09:56,490
 Strangely, I'm drawn to you 

893
01:09:56,490 --> 01:09:58,660
 Nobody will understand me 

894
01:09:58,660 --> 01:10:01,730
[Young Lady and Gentleman]

895
01:10:01,730 --> 01:10:05,930
Chief Jo Noona, I just cannot understand. I've committed a mortal sin.

896
01:10:05,930 --> 01:10:07,850
What do you mean?

897
01:10:07,850 --> 01:10:11,740
Does Lawyer Koh know that the much younger young woman is Ms. Park?

898
01:10:11,740 --> 01:10:13,350
I will check it for myself.

899
01:10:13,350 --> 01:10:15,290
I am here for an interview for the driver's position. Which way should I go?

900
01:10:15,290 --> 01:10:18,630
Delicious chicken skewers are 5 thousand won for ten...

901
01:10:18,630 --> 01:10:21,300
Don't think about anything else, just come with me.

902
01:10:21,300 --> 01:10:22,370
Se Ryun.

903
01:10:22,370 --> 01:10:25,380
Whatever they do with each other, why do I have to care?

904
01:10:25,380 --> 01:10:27,210
Ms. Park Noona! Ms. Park Noona!

905
01:10:27,210 --> 01:10:30,770
Didn't you see me? I wanted to talk to someone about it.

906
01:10:30,770 --> 01:10:33,180
It's about my friend, not me.

907
01:10:33,180 --> 01:10:36,550
Your invitation for me to go to the US with you, is that still valid?

908
01:10:36,550 --> 01:10:40,700
I no longer want to live trying to match a life I don't remember.

909
01:10:40,700 --> 01:10:44,400
I cannot marry you, Chief Jo Noona.
